caption: Ordered the following food; pansit bihon /canton combo, kare-kare, pork Adobo, bistek tagalog.  We wasted our time and money because none of these foods taste good. Don't be fool with pictures alone. The pansit tasted not only bad but it was undercooked,  the kare kare tasted left over fried pork with kare sauce,  the pork Adobo tasted old fried pork and smells bad, which surprisingly adobo should smell good bec of bay leaf and will taste good regardless of storing in ref for 2 or few days. The bistek tagalog was the only one we were able to eat just because we were too hungry already. FRUSTRATED.
I visit this place a lot since I work close by. I must say their customer service is always good and they keep the spot well kept consistently. Prices are affordable and they serve large portions.

So I heard many great things about this place cause they have great delicious food but went here for their halo halo in which typical Filipino restaurants and or even if prepared at home the specific desert halo halo usually comes with an ube/taro ice cream on top. Well I ordered 4 halo halo in which all had vanilla ice cream for almost $8 a cup I would think that it would at least come like a traditional halo halo but it didn’t. I never tasted it with vanilla ice cream with it but tried it, which the ice cream tasted freezer burnt and when I verified the menu it did say vanilla and an up charge for the ube flavor, I thought it was strange to be charge for more when first of all the halo halo did not taste as good as it was priced.
Best pare food
Food was good we always ordered the Caldereta. Lately the portion of the calderera was cut in half. It used to feed a family of four and now you have to order 3. Not worth it anymore.
Awesome environment and super welcoming service. The food was fresh and delightful. Will absolutely recommend this place to friends. Convenient prices and large meals. Keep up the great work.

We are not Philippino, but are Asian Americans, and we ordered: - pork adobo (saucy) - crispy pata (pork) - beef nilaga (soup) - garlic fried rice (fragrant) - halo halo dessert  And it was AMAZINGLY DELICIOUS!! It's the kind of place that makes you feel like you're having a home cooked meal, one that you've long for a long time. Please support local businesses, eat well and tip heavy.

The shrimp pancit canton was awesome.  Sadly, they no longer have barbeque of any kind.  I would have liked some kind of uncooked vegetable dish, like lumpiang sariwa.  If you go in for pickup, the COVID-19 precautions they have set up, while effective, need some polishing in the esthetics department.
The place offers a fantastic variety of fresh food. I love eating here. Employees are always very kind, rates are reasonable and the place is always neat.
One of my favorite places to grab some food. good location, well organised, and excellent customer service. Keep it up!

We like a lot hanging out. Last night we  found this fine restaurant which friends recommended to us. We spent a delightful experience there with superb dishes and a nice stuff and a great  cuisine. We put this venue in our list  and we shall surely come back soon.  Highly recommended.
Great food. I have nothing else to say! :)
This place is worth trying. They have big portions for reasonable rates. Always well organized and with excellent atmosphere. Will visit here again.
I visit this spot a lot since I work close by. I like how the customer service is always excellent and they keep the spot clean constantly. Prices are fair and they serve generous portions.
Exceptional and flavorful food, I loved the character this spot has, and the staff members were very nice. Will definitely come back in the future.
This place has fantastic service as well as enjoyable meals. One of my favourite restaurants in the city. The food and drinks served rapidly and the rates are inexpensive. Highly recommended.
Fantastic and flavorful food, I liked the vibes this place has, and the staff members were super nice. Will surely visit here again.
The menu and service were beyond my expectations. We truly loved the vibes of this place. First-rate place to take the family out for lunch.
I constantly come purchasing some food here. I love the speedy customer service and well cooked food. Keep it up.
Great food, kind employees, constantly great vibes. They charge convenient rates and the food quality is awesome. I recommend this place.
I actually enjoyed their dishes and service, good area very close to my house. The employees are always friendly. Would recommend to others.
Had a very good experience in this place with my daughter. The food arrived rapidly and the service is just excellent. Prices are fair.
Extraordinary environment and super friendly service. The menu was crisp and yummy. Will clearly recommend this place to my friends. Fair prices and generous portions. Keep it up.
Love this place especially their crispy PATA. Please Check out my YouTube Channel REY JACKSON PINOY IN CHICAGO i made a video . Please don't forget to  SUBSCRIBE! Thank you!
First-rate environment and very personal service. The menu was fresh and enchanting. Will surely recommend this spot to others. Reasonable prices and generous meals. Good job.
Just like lola's 🥺

I celebrated my graduation yesterday in this great place. happy to tell that we passed a incredible evening and the place was surely one of the reasons for the happy gathering. The stuff  collaborated in a splendid style, the meals were yummy and my buddies were very  happy. We shall surely visit again for more celebrations. Thank you very much.

This place offers excellent service and delightful food. My favourite restaurant ever. The meals arrived quick and the prices were fair. Highly recommended.
Best place to get food when in a hurry. Their customer service is efficient, pricing is reasonable, excellent character. Highly recommended
This spot is fantastic! Good rates, big portions and the staff members are always super nice.
Excellent and tasty food, I loved the vibes the spot has, and the staff members were very nice. I will surely come back again.

Food is ok but service is aweful. Went to dine in for 2. A big group was right behind us about 10 people. Got our orders in first. We ordered 2 meals and an appetizer. Everyone from the big group got their food and was almost done eating and we still didnt get out food until I went to ask to cancel it. Apparently it was done and been sitting on the counter so we told them to pack it to go. And they still took forever to pack it. It was over an hour wait overall. Terrible customer service. Didnt get offer discount or anything, at least they apologized I guess. First and last time eating there.

I love this restaurant! They have superb dishes, their menu is nice, The chef in that spot is an expert, I love a lot eating all their dishes. The dishes are always of high qualtity, the service towards the clients  is very good too. I  go often to this restaurant and I was never disappointed. I recommend this place.
Sig sig is off the chain.....

I like this spot! They serve marvelous food, they have a rich menu, The cook in that place is a specialist, I love very much eating all their food. The food is always good, the service towards the guests  is nice. I often eat in this restaurant and I was never unsatisfied. I recommend this place.

First of all, they always turn their Uber Eats app off for some reasons. We had to call and “request” for them to turn it on just so we can order, all the time. It kinda felt like we’re begging for food.  Today, we decided to just drive over there for a pick up and call in advance so that it will save us time waiting for our order. After getting my order, the lady told me it’ll take 45 minutes. When we usually dine in there, it takes way less time than that. So I asked her courteously, if they can please start making the order now since I am just 15 minutes away from their place. Then all of sudden said “oh I’m sorry but we are not accepting advanced order anymore”. I got confused and just decided to go there and place my order once I got there, as opposed to saving 15 minutes. Thank you Kawayan for being so accomodating.
Small but feels at home and good food
The food was ok. 🤷

Very friendly family own place.  You can see them cooking from the seating area.  Dine in service can be slow if you are eating in but it's worth it.  I was told the owners were part owners of Filipinana before they closed.   If you liked their food, you'll like the food here.
The place offers a large range of delicious food. I enjoy eating here. Staff members are always friendly, pricing is convenient and the spot is always neat.

First time customer, ordered thru Grub Hub. Food arrived early, but cold.  Meat was tough and nothing tasted good except the rice. Called to complain and woman said “no refund, Grub Hub got the money not us”. Terrible customer service.  Had to contact Grub Hub to settle our complaint. Terrible customer service, especially since it was our first order.

I really love the halo2x here..super creamy and less ice..some restaurant's halo2x has more ice than the other ingredients..

Great place for traditional Filipino food. The pork sinigang and garlic fried rice are my go-to's and some of my favorites on the menu but I haven't had anything I didn't like. The service is quick and the portions are sizeable and good for sharing. I recommend ordering a few things and eating family style. They also do take out and catering and we have never been disappointed. I definitely recommend stopping in.

Great authentic little Filipino place. There are not many in the Chicago area to choose from in spite of the fact that there is a large Filipino population here. I cannot recommend this place more highly.
Food was great and tasted like home!
Delicious classic Pinoy dishes. My mom loved it.
Friendly service the kitchen cooks are from Philippines the food it's  delicious I suggest to order the Kaldereta wit a side of steam white rice. For dessert authentic leche flan

I ordered thru grub hub, delivery was quick but the food was terrible.  The fried rice and the noodles were too greasy...the tocino was burnt and tough! It was way different than when we dined in.  I guess they don’t really care much for online orders which is too bad! 😏👎
Love this place

Great food and service. Will return when in town again.

This place has great Filipino food friendlier than most pinoy restos around Chicago.  Love the lechon kawali and crispy pata. They have good lumpia. It's right in Veterans square in Jefferson  park. It's good home cooking get some Kari Kari or pinok bit it's all good. Kozy seating bring a friend 4 da food!
Better than other Filipino Restaurants...foods are great and the only server is very nice.

Keep coming back to this gem by north of Chicago. Home style Filipino cooking leaving your belly and heart fulfilled. Really an authentic Pinoy cuisine at at very affordable price. My boyfriend and I loved their beef sinigang, kare kare and daing na bangus. Servings are good for 2-3 people which is not bad. It’s a small eatery with a homey ambiance of the Philippines. Service is prompt and friendly staff!

Food is good but during our visit they called the maintenance to fix the damn door and the draft is blowing on my face the whole time, they couldn't have arrange this at the right time... so that being said my dining experience is walang kwenta! At least there's mobile service here 😁👏😣 so that's good!
Food was good but portion is small and pricey

Good food and value for your money. Great service as well. I was eating my order 20 minutes after i placed them. I ordered Pancit Canton and it looks very good but I found it salty for my taste. Maybe there should also be a Chicken option for the Pancit. The Shanghai Lumpia taste great as well as the Leche Flan.

Closest taste to the Filipino food back home. Good service and open late on Sundays (9 pm). Ample sitting although I expect this place to be crowded during peak times. Good food and just the right serving. The staff needs to be a little more cheerful and friendly just in my opinion but nothing biggy.

This place will definitely surprise you. I love their menu.  Had the combo pancit and adobe chicken. Wow!!!   Shangai egg rolls are banging!!  Smells terrific in here.  Next Im going to try the bicol express (coconut milk stewed w seafood.   So mad I've only just now started coming here

Let me start off with saying I was very surprised and happy with this place my sister-in-law had gone previously and said it was good the stuff and owners with very friendly the food cooked to order and fresh and good we ordered to much that we had to take some home so we had leftovers very good probably the best Filipino restaurant I've bean to in Chicago

The food is great the service is horrible! When you walk into a food establishment there's an expectation of providing high service regardless how well your business is doing. Ikaw pa ang lalapit sa kanila to ask questions the lady in the cashier was not very welcoming nor seemed knowledgeable of what she is doing. Its a small establishment that lacks great service! And you should not have old people at the front store. Lol That alone says alot.
Great food

This Filipino restaurant offers authentic Filipino cuisine. They have very good Crispy Pata and Dinuguan. Prices are reasonable bit you are thinking of eating there it would be good to call ahead and put in your order and make the reservation. The wait is long when you order because they have to accommodate all the other take out orders. If they could hire more cook and have the take out order separate  shortening the wait time....but the food is worth the wait...just dont come very hungry..
Great food! Best Halo-Halo ever! I drive all the way from the suburbs to get their food and definitely worth the drive!!

This place is authentic Northern Filipino cuisine. .what is known as Tagalog. Portions are Big.. the Chicken Inasal (barbeque) is Not tasty like it is at Bacolod or other places in Niles. It's always over burned with lack of seasoning. Soups are way too salty. I haven't tried the pork dishes. Service was Good and accommodating, yet the wait can get long on the weekends.
Great food, interesting menu. All menu items are Filipino. This place replaced Ron's Grill.
